President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed May 2023 as National Physical Fitness and Sports Month in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of regular exercise in improving physical and mental health, reducing the risk of diseases, and fostering social connection. It also highlights the disparities in access to exercise opportunities faced by certain communities, such as those affected by diet-related diseases, low-income families, and students. The proclamation outlines various initiatives and partnerships aimed at increasing access to physical activity, including the expansion of parks, improvements to community spaces, and investments in infrastructure. President Biden calls on all Americans to prioritize daily physical activity and support efforts to make sports opportunities more accessible in their communities. The proclamation is part of broader efforts to promote a healthier and more resilient society.